<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 19 at 2:59PM CDT  by NWS Birmingham</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of southern Randolph,
northeastern Tallapoosa and northwestern Chambers Counties through
330 PM CDT...
At 259 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from New Site to near Sparkling Springs. Movement
was east at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Roanoke, New Site, Wadley, Goldville, Abanda, Crystal Lake, Sparkling
Springs, Daviston, Dickert, Roanoke Municipal Airport, Motley and
Rock Mills.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
